cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CE 

The paper proposes a new unsupervised and semi-supervised technique for machine learning, which suggests it could fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of the FICO machine learning challenge dataset and the focus on explaining decisions in the financial industry could also place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of the MAPPER algorithm to build simplicial complexes suggests a potential fit with cs.CE (Computational Geometry).
